claim.claim-text:
1. A method for automatic media population of a style presentation, comprising:
collecting a plurality of presentation media, wherein a user is enabled to collect the presentation media via a user interface, and wherein each of the presentation media has one of a plurality of data types;
positioning the collected presentation media on a storyboard viewable on the user interface; and
selecting a style presentation having one or more presentation elements, wherein the user is allowed to select the style presentation from a presentation styles menu, and wherein each of the presentation elements accepts a corresponding data type;
wherein the selection of the style presentation results in the automatic population of the one or more presentation elements of the style presentation with the presentation media positioned on the storyboard having the corresponding data type, wherein the presentation media with the corresponding data type are identified without user input by searching the storyboard to find one or more of the collected presentation media having the data type that is accepted by each of the presentation elements.

6. A system for automatic media population of a style presentation, comprising:
a storage device;
a processing element having a processing program and access to the storage device; and
a process-readable medium having executable instructions thereon to direct the processing system when used by the processing element to:
collect a plurality of presentation media, wherein a user is enabled to collect the presentation media via a user interface, and wherein each of the presentation media has one of a plurality of data types;
position the collected presentation media on a storyboard viewable on the user interface; and
select a style presentation having one or more presentation elements, wherein the user is allowed to select the style presentation from a presentation styles menu, and wherein each of the presentation elements accepts a corresponding data type;
wherein the selection of the style presentation results in the automatic population of the one or more presentation elements of the style presentation with the presentation media positioned on the storyboard having the corresponding data type, wherein the presentation media with the corresponding data type are without user input by a search of the storyboard to find one or more of the collected presentation media having the data type that is accepted by each of the presentation elements.

11. A non-transitory computer-readable medium having computer executable instructions for performing a method comprising:
collecting a plurality of presentation media, wherein a user is enabled to collect the presentation media via a user interface, and wherein each of the presentation media has one of a plurality of data types;
positioning the collected presentation media on a storyboard viewable on the user interface; and
selecting a style presentation having one or more presentation elements, wherein the user is allowed to select the style presentation from a presentation styles menu, and wherein each of the presentation elements accepts a corresponding data type;
wherein the selection of the style presentation results in the automatic population of the one or more presentation elements of the style presentation with the presentation media positioned on the storyboard having the corresponding data type, wherein the presentation media with the corresponding data type are identified without user input by searching the storyboard to find one or more of the collected presentation media having the data type that is accepted by each of the presentation elements.
